# UI Components Guide

The project uses a set of reusable UI components located in the `components/ui` directory. These components are built using a modern design system.

## Core Components
- `Button`: A versatile button component with various states (default, loading, disabled)
- `Input`: Form input component with support for different types
- `NavigationMenu`: Complex navigation component with dropdown support

## Component Usage
The components are styled using Tailwind CSS and follow a consistent design pattern. They support:
- Dark/light mode
- Responsive design
- Accessibility features
- Loading states
- Error states

## Navigation Structure
The application uses a consistent navigation pattern:
- Sticky header with logo
- Main navigation links
- Dropdown menu for AI tools
- Mobile-responsive design

## Design System
The UI follows these design principles:
- Clean and minimal interface
- Consistent spacing and typography
- Clear visual hierarchy
- Interactive feedback on user actions
